	"class": "vulnerability",
	"metadata": {
		"title": "kernel: drm/amd/display: Correct the defined value for AMDGPU_DMUB_NOTIFICATION_MAX (moderate)",
		"reference": [
			{
				"ref_id": "CVE-2024-46871",
				"ref_url": "https://access.redhat.com/security/cve/CVE-2024-46871",
				"source": "CVE"
			}
		],
		"description": "DOCUMENTATION: A flaw was found in the AMD Radeon graphics card driver in the Linux kernel. Out-of-bounds access can be triggered due to arrays being created based on the wrong number of maximum DMUB notification types available, resulting in a denial of service. \n            STATEMENT: Under normal conditions, unprivileged local users cannot trigger this issue and the system must have an AMD GPU, limiting the impact of this vulnerability.\n\nAdditionally, this issue is known to impact only the availability of the system with no other relevant security impact.\n            MITIGATION: Mitigation for this issue is either not available or the currently available options do not meet the Red Hat Product Security criteria comprising ease of use and deployment, applicability to widespread installation base or stability.",
